descript.abstract: U.S. GDT Institutions (Hospitals) represents point locations for hospitals and medical centers within the United States.
descript.purpose: U.S. GDT Institutions (Hospitals) provides the locations and names for hospitals and medical centers within the United States.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:100,000.

distinfo.techpreq: To use this data requires software that supports ArcView® GIS shapefiles.

procstep.procdesc: The data set was created from a variety of different data sources. These ranged from local municipal maps to TIGER/Line files.

The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted data set from GDT Dynamap/2000 v9.0. Converted to North American Datum of 1983 (NAD83) (except Hawaii which remains in Old Hawaiian Datum). Changed attribute names and their order. Removed unneeded attributes. Created projection file (.prj). Ran ArcView Avenue request ExportClean, and created spatial indices.

horizpa.horizpar: The positional accuracy matches or is better than the positional accuracy of the TIGER/Line coordinates. The positional accuracy of the TIGER/Line coordinates at best is +/- 167 feet approximately.

dataqual.logic: No duplicate features are present. The shapefile is exported using Avenue request ExportClean. This request verifies and enforces the correctness of shapes.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
